Wire frontend images to CMS/S3 and tighten image pipeline

- Home page: group logo, featured project image, and owner photo now load
  from CMS settings/projects/team data (with static fallbacks)
- Country pages (Kuwait/UAE/China/Egypt): hero image and corner logo read
  from Country.country_image_url and Country.logo_url by slug
- About page: the 4 "What we offer" tiles now source images from CMS Services
  in sort_order
- Contact page: align to current Country schema (name_en/name_ar)
- next.config.ts: disable Next image optimizer for remote assets (S3 is already
  web-ready; avoids TimeoutError floods from the eu-north-1 bucket) and
  declare allowed image qualities [75, 90, 100]
- .gitignore: expand editor/OS/cache patterns, ignore archives and local
  uploads directories to prevent large-file pushes
